4e24b84fcf0021942ca17af6954356.png\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/assets/static/twitter-clone-copilot.42db587.124e24b84fcf0021942ca17af6954356.png\" width=\"2560\" alt=\"Twitter clone Copilot\"></noscript></p>\n<p>This was a true “WOW” moment. The app was well-styled, functional, and featured everything I asked for. The process took around 1.5 hours, whereas doing it by hand would have likely taken me 6-7 hours. A significant time-saver!</p>\n<h2 id=\"cursor\"><a href=\"#cursor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Cursor</h2>\n<p>Next, I tried the same exercise with Cursor, providing the same initial prompt. Cursor managed to deliver a working Django application in one-shot, something Copilot had failed to do. Not only that, but the resulting application was of better quality, particularly in terms of styling. It had even added the ability to add images to tweets without explicitly asking for it.</p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 2560 1471' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-368f431bbc1c829de449476663031605'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-368f431bbc1c829de449476663031605)' width='2560' height='1471' xlink:href='data:image/png%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAAAlCAYAAADyUO83AAAACXBIWXMAABYlAAAWJQFJUiTwAAAHk0lEQVR42t1ZSW8cRRT2lUgc2ASIJWwKy4kDy4ULCIk/gMQFIcQBCSkQEhQCSYBIEcuBReLGJkAc2G8g8QMCIontxHHibTyeGY/HM56lZ3qb3qrq473q7pn2lngZwElLn6td1VX93lev33v1ZmjXSy52vSxx1V6BXXslIW6v2idw3aEI9xyRuItwx%2bEY1%2byX2POWxG1vSNzwmsT1BwjUXnsgHrv5IN1Te/U%2bXlMma/674PfceHC5LIzrDsSyxPqtPXfo2lfceMJ%2bkQH9fzDCLUcjPPSuwMPvCTxwTOCR9wV2vynwKLUPHpe47x2JWw/FBN19JL7f85bAnYcFbjoocM2rYsW6ydrbglgTdx%2bVuOdovEksx%2b43pe678zCTIdadN3QqZ%2bNsKVyFM0VuBUZKEiNFhsAwYawsqZU4X